The paper discusses the application of reinforcement learning in a first-person shooter game, which involves decision-making in real-time. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of 3D environments and shooting skills, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the reward mechanism and decision-making strategies, which could be relevant to game theory (cs.GT).
